# 4. Architecture Overview
 
CRP organizes perception into layers that mirror biological sensory-cognitive architecture:
 
```
┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│  RAW OBSERVATION (screenshot, screen state, audio, etc.)    │
└──────────────────────────┬──────────────────────────────────┘
                           │
               ┌───────────▼───────────┐
               │   LAYER 0: SENSES     │  Parallel, fast, general-purpose
               │                       │
               │  Visual    Textual    │  Each sense produces structured
               │  Temporal  Contextual │  output from raw observation
               │  Auditory             │
               └───────────┬───────────┘
                           │ sensory outputs
               ┌───────────▼───────────┐
               │ LAYER 0.5: MEMORY     │  Automatic context priming
               │   CONTEXT PRIMING     │
               │                       │  Assembles relevant history
               │  Episodic retrieval   │  based on sensory outputs
               │  Pattern matching     │
               │  Instinct recall      │
               └───────────┬───────────┘
                           │ sensory + memory context
               ┌───────────▼───────────┐
               │  LAYER 1: AFFECT      │  Emotional pre-processing
               │                       │
               │  Valence  Arousal     │  Generates affect from senses
               │  Familiarity Urgency  │  + memory context
               └───────────┬───────────┘
                           │ sensory + memory + affect
               ┌───────────▼───────────┐
               │  LAYER 2: COGNITION   │  Parallel broadcast to all
               │                       │  cognitive modules
               │  Safety   Task        │
               │  Anomaly  Intent      │  Each receives full context:
               │  Learning Compliance  │  sensory + memory + affect
               │  Social   Domain      │
               └───────────┬───────────┘
                           │ responses (assertion/query/null/override/resolve)
               ┌───────────▼───────────┐
               │  LAYER 3: MEMORY      │  Post-cycle storage
               │   FORMATION           │
               │                       │  Salience-weighted encoding
               │  Channel assignment   │  Affect-colored decay rates
               │  Decay configuration  │
               └───────────────────────┘
```
 
Key architectural principle: **senses are general and stable; cognition is specialized and extensible.** Sensory systems change rarely and serve all cognitive consumers. Cognitive modules specialize by domain, multiply per vertical, and can be deployed independently. This creates a natural deployment boundary: senses run locally (fast heuristics), cognition can run anywhere.
 
