# Appendix A: Example Cycle (v0.2.0)
 
**Scenario**: User is on CheckpointEHR billing screen with a denied claim showing red indicators.
 
```
Step 1 — Sensory Transduction (parallel, <50ms total):
  Visual:     { dominant_color: "red", alert_badges: 2, modal: false, layout: "data_table" }
  Textual:    { entities: ["Angelita Edgerton", "ICD-10: F32.1", "CPT: 90837", "DENIED"],
                structure: "table_with_status_column", density: 0.7, register: "clinical" }
  Temporal:   { time_on_page: 8s, session_duration: 45min, pace: "normal", time_of_day: "afternoon" }
  Contextual: { app: "CheckpointEHR", page: "CP Central - Billing", workspace: "claims_review" }
 
Step 2 — Memory Context Priming (<20ms):
  Context Frame:
    recent: "Last 5 observations were all in CheckpointEHR billing"
    patterns: "User reviews denied claims Mon/Wed afternoons"
    instincts: [{ id: "inst-44a", hint: "Modifier issue with this payer — unresolved from yesterday" }]
    anomalies: "2 claims denied for same payer this week"
 
Step 3 — Affect Pre-Processing:
  valence: -0.4   (red indicators, "DENIED" text)
  arousal: 0.6    (action required, elevated density)
  familiarity: 0.8 (user does this regularly on Wed afternoons)
  urgency: 0.5    (needs attention, not emergency)
 
Step 4 — Priority Adjustment:
  era.core.safety:   0.95 → 0.95 (unaffected — always high)
  era.core.anomaly:  0.60 → 0.78 (boosted by negative valence + unresolved instinct)
